This paper presents a new approach for object detection using keypoint-based methods. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework that improves both precision and recall, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could make it relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the MS-COCO dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
